        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 7:05PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pickwick Dam, or over Pickwick Landing State Park, moving northwest
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shiloh National Military Park, Pickwick Dam, Hamburg, Crump,
Phillips, Bruton Branch, Pickwick Landing State Park, Hurley,
Walkertown, Red Sulphur Springs, Counce, Mount Vinson, New Lawton,
Damon, Savannah, Southside, Pittsburg Landing, Childers Hill,
Gilchrist, and West Shihloh.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
